--- !u!114 &452185250
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 452185248}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "<color=#C9A7FF><b>Thank you for exploring this tool</b></color>\r\n\r\n<color=#E7EAF0>This
    calculator is part of the wider Omnisyndetic Open Research Programme. It is designed
    to let the underlying geometric object be inspected directly, rather than treated
    as a black box.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#9AA3B2>The register and ledger are fixed
    first. From that single derived structure, flavour content, charge tier, certified
    seat, admitted \u03BB interval, and the corresponding rest-energy band are read
    off deterministically.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#8FCFC8>In practical use, you enter
    the flavour and charge structure of a baryon state and the tool returns the deterministic
    mass band assigned by the ledger. The \u03BB control then lets you probe points
    inside the admitted interval, so you can check whether a measured baryon mass
    is contained within the certified band.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#9AA3B2>The purpose
    of the tool is containment and audit, not point-mass fitting. The midpoint shown
    in the display is a visual reference for the interval. It is not a claim of exact
    point prediction or a fitted best-value estimate.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#8FCFC8>No
    intrinsic mass inputs are used to generate the band itself. The construction
    is parameter-free at the level of derivation: the band is fixed by the geometric
    object and its ledger rules. \u03BB probing is then used as an interpretive read-off
    inside the admitted interval, not as a hidden tuning mechanism added to force
    the result.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#9AA3B2>This also means the tool can be used
    beyond the present audit set. As further ground states are established experimentally,
    the same fixed object can be checked against them in exactly the same way.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#E7EAF0>This
    remains an ongoing open research project, and your interest, care, and scrutiny
    are genuinely appreciated. Thank you for taking the time to explore it.</color>"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
